    <description>This game simulates the famous battle of Minias Thirith in the 3rd Book of Lord of The Rings, by JRR Tolkien.&amp;#10;This is a FREE wargame available in Portuguese.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The sequence of the game will be divided into turns, with at total of 15 turns.  Each turn corresponds to one day of real time. The events of this wargame take place from March 07 through March 21 of the Third Age.&amp;#10;Each turn will be divided in two stages and each stage corresponds with a single action of one of the armies.&amp;#10;The first stage is always the player who controls the Western Alliance.  The Western Alliance consists of Gondor, Rohan, Dol Amroth, Dunedain, Lebennim, and Laledon.  For the sake of simplicity, this player will be called GONDOR.  The opposing player controls the forces of Sauron consisting of the armies from Mordor, Harad, and the men of the east called Easterlings.  This player will be called MORDOR.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each stage is divided in 3 sequential phases, representing the grouping of similar actions. The Preparation Phase, the Movement Phase, and the Combat Phase.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After 15 turns the player with the most points wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
